⊢ experiment-0
  given hypothesis ≡ "H2: Projects adopted as dependencies by popular frameworks..."
  given experiment-desc ≡ "E2: libraries.io dependency data..."
  yield result, supports-hypothesis

  ∴ Simulate running E2 to test H2...

-- LLM evaluation (simulated):

  yield result ≡ "Analysis of 45 npm packages adopted by React, Vue, or Angular between 2018-2020 vs 45 matched controls: adopted packages saw 4.2x median contributor growth over 3 years (p<0.001). Download counts grew 8.7x vs 1.3x for controls. However, 6 of 45 adopted packages (13%) still died — they were replaced by alternatives that the framework switched to. The dependency flywheel is powerful but not unconditional; it can reverse if the upstream framework drops you."

  yield supports-hypothesis ≡ "supports"

-- oracle checks:
--   ⊨ result describes concrete findings → ✓ (specific numbers, sample sizes)
--   ⊨ supports-hypothesis ∈ { "supports", "refutes", "inconclusive" } → ✓

