  given experiment-desc ≡ "E3: Scrape repos for contributor onboarding signals..."
  yield result, supports-hypothesis

  ∴ Simulate running E3 to test H3...

-- LLM evaluation (simulated):

  yield result ≡ "Of 500 GitHub repos sampled across Python and JavaScript ecosystems: repos with CONTRIBUTING.md had 1.8x higher first-time contributor return rate. Repos with good-first-issue labels: 2.1x. Repos with both: 2.7x. But the 3-5x claim in H3 is overstated — onboarding friction explains ~22% of variance in return rate, below the 30% threshold. More importantly, contributor retention alone predicted project survival with only 0.41 AUC, barely above chance. Projects died for other reasons (maintainer burnout, ecosystem shift) even with high retention."

  yield supports-hypothesis ≡ "inconclusive"

-- oracle checks:
--   ⊨ result describes concrete findings → ✓
