-- LLM evaluation (simulated):

  yield result ≡ "Of 87 projects where the primary maintainer went inactive for 6+ months: funded projects (Open Collective or corporate, n=31) survived at 74% rate vs unfunded (n=56) at 32%. The effect was strongest for corporate-backed projects (82% survival) vs donation-funded (61%). However, causation is ambiguous: corporate-backed projects may have been more important to begin with, attracting both funding AND successor maintainers. A notable counter-example: left-pad (unfunded) was immediately forked and maintained by the community because of extreme dependency centrality."

  yield supports-hypothesis ≡ "supports"

