  yield experiments[]

-- LLM evaluation (simulated):

  yield experiments ≡ [
    "E2' (tests H2'): Identify packages that were DROPPED by a framework (e.g., moment.js by many frameworks in favor of date-fns). Track contributor trajectory after being dropped. If >50% lose significant contributors within 1 year, supports the fragility clause of H2'.",
    "E3' (tests H3'): Control for ecosystem centrality. Among projects with EQUAL dependency counts, does onboarding quality predict survival? If yes, H3' stands. If no, onboarding is merely correlated with well-managed projects.",
    "E4' (tests H4'): Distinguish causation from correlation. Compare projects that RECEIVED corporate funding after initial growth vs projects that had corporate funding from inception. If late-funded projects survive at similar rates, suggests funding is causal. If only early-funded survive, suggests selection bias.",
    "E5 (tests H5): Measure ecosystem centrality (PageRank in the dependency graph) for 1000 projects. Correlate with 5-year survival. If centrality alone explains >50% of survival variance, H5 is the dominant factor."
  ]

